    <bioghist>Ann Arbor, Mich., engineer. Historian of the Miller and Lunden families, and of the Lewiston area of Michigan.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Reminiscence of his life and other topics. Titles include: "My experience in the Army Air Force, 1943 to 1946" (typescript and CD-ROM); "Farming North of Lewiston, Michigan, 1910-1960..."; and "The Civilian Conservation Corps in Michigan"; also collected World War II letters written to his mother by her cousin Carl (Bud) Hallenius; correspondence and other papers (1975-1981) relating to Miller's support for nuclear power; reminiscences of Salling, Michigan of Clarence Cross; and visual materials.</scopecontent>
